    <lmp:Comment type="FUNCTION">Reduces the level of nuclear PKM isoform M2 which results in repression of cyclin CCND1 transcription and reduced cell growth</lmp:Comment>
    <lmp:Comment type="SUBUNIT">Interacts with NRBP1 (PubMed:22510880). Interacts with PKM isoform M2; the interaction results in reduced nuclear levels of PKM isoform M2, leading to repression of cyclin CCND1 transcription and reduced cell growth (PubMed:27573352). Interacts with WDR77 (PubMed:27337956)</lmp:Comment>
    <lmp:Comment type="MISCELLANEOUS">May be involved in the loss of cell cycle regulation in colorectal tumors, expression is shown to be decreased in the majority of tumors</lmp:Comment>
